  "texts": [
    "Since H is flat and ρ(π 1 (B)) ≤ Aut(N), there is a totally geodesic section σ: (B, g B) → (M, g).",
    "Thus, local homogeneity of (M, g) implies local homogeneity of (B, g B) since a totally geodesic submanifold of a locally homogeneous space is itself locally homogeneous.",
    "Low-dimensional solitons 5.1.",
    "Dimension 4.",
    "In this section, we apply the results of §4 to give a complete description of the Ricci solitons arising as limits of four-dimensional immortal Ricci flows."
